<paragraph id="A64FE163904CEC5F66B0DE23B5681D4D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="C10C8A8695D6F3DA3D1FDB9149B374CE" LSID="FE829B88F4F85051A601B10DCC0C5256" authority="Y. X. Liu, Zi Y. Liu &amp; K. D. Hyde, Phytotaxa 103 (1): 53 (2013)" family="Shiraiaceae" higherTaxonomySource="treatment-meta" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Shiraiaceae Y.X. Liu, Zi Y. Liu &amp; K.D. Hyde, Phytotaxa 103(1): 53 (2013)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1F9F137C34230ADC1478EDEACDE712B9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="12CEB822E387BEAD6B7E3DE9CDF10A01" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="745CEB9CAFE0CC83C26497EDA3D6C5FF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The family 
<taxonomicName id="68CA8936B876EC417ED9CEEDDA3EB09F" family="Shiraiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Shiraiaceae</taxonomicName>
was introduced by 
<bibRefCitation id="B90EB9508CD15B25319756E38C9E66A1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" author="Liu, YX" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="51 - 60" refId="B34" refString="Liu, YX, Hyde, KD, Ariyawansa, HA, Li, WJ, Zhou, DQ, Yang, YL, Chen, YM, Liu, ZY, 2013. Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota). . Phytotaxa 103: 51 - 60" title="Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" volume="103" year="2013">Liu et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
with a single genus and later 
<taxonomicName id="4B30F337DEED63978634EECA92F75795" class="Dothideomycetes" genus="Grandigallia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Grandigallia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Grandigallia</taxonomicName>
was added to this family by 
<bibRefCitation id="0F1BB6B805BC407D710C4C28B7F53418" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.147.2.1" author="Ariyawansa, HA" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="35 - 47" refId="B2" refString="Ariyawansa, HA, Kang, JC, Alias, SA, Chukeatirote, E, Hyde, KD, 2013. Towards a natural classification of Dothideomycetes: The genera Dermatodothella, Dothideopsella, Grandigallia, Hysteropeltella and Gloeodiscus (Dothideomycetesincertae sedis). . Phytotaxa 147: 35 - 47" title="Towards a natural classification of Dothideomycetes: The genera Dermatodothella, Dothideopsella, Grandigallia, Hysteropeltella and Gloeodiscus (Dothideomycetesincertae sedis)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.147.2.1" volume="147" year="2013">Ariyawansa et al. (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. In previous studies, 
<taxonomicName id="90CC12EC3F67DACC3E6BE8831B8031D4" family="Shiraiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Shiraiaceae</taxonomicName>
was closely related with 
<taxonomicName id="12C8F7E741CEB4A4076A8228575512DA" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Phaeosphaeriaceae</taxonomicName>
and their distinction was questionable (
<bibRefCitation id="4CA6EEBDB401C6FA04FD9698F4C27CBB" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/jobm.200410434" author="Cheng, TF" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Basic Microbiology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="339 - 350" refId="B9" refString="Cheng, TF, Jia, XM, Ma, XH, Lin, HP, Zhao, YH, 2004. Phylogenetic study on Shiraiabambusicola by rDNA sequence analyses. . Journal of Basic Microbiology 44: 339 - 350" title="Phylogenetic study on Shiraiabambusicola by rDNA sequence analyses." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/jobm.200410434" volume="44" year="2004">Cheng et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="B56348789002B7F21C984BC76410652D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" author="Liu, YX" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="51 - 60" refId="B34" refString="Liu, YX, Hyde, KD, Ariyawansa, HA, Li, WJ, Zhou, DQ, Yang, YL, Chen, YM, Liu, ZY, 2013. Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota). . Phytotaxa 103: 51 - 60" title="Shiraiaceae, new family of Pleosporales (Dothideomycetes, Ascomycota)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.103.1.4" volume="103" year="2013">Liu et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). However, our multi-gene analyses (
<figureCitation id="75F6CE66BD1DDA36C6B103842B2B50EF" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Maximum likelihood phylogenetic tree generated from RAxML (GTR + G model), based on combined LSU, SSU, TEF 1 and RPB 2 sequences data. ML values (MLBP) (&gt; 50 %), resulting from 1000 bootstrap replicates and Bayesian posterior probabilities (BYPP) greater than 0.90, are given at the nodes. The original isolate numbers' codes are noted after the species names. The tree is rooted to Dothidea insculpta (CBS 189.58). Ex-type or ex-epitype strains are in bold. Newly generated strains are in red and the new genus is in yellow background." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.58.36723.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/329243" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) clearly indicate that 
<taxonomicName id="6290D811E2B2D9D8395A2C96E31D4802" family="Shiraiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Shiraiaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BDC4700309325D4EE3045C997419136B" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Phaeosphaeriaceae</taxonomicName>
are distinct. Evidence is also borne out by the fact the 
<taxonomicName id="3AB1545C684BE24FCF370D971EF45456" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Phaeosphaeriaceae</taxonomicName>
have single ascostromata (
<bibRefCitation id="AF340497837B4F3A58A2E503E1593811" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-014-0308-3" author="Phookamsak, R" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="159 - 238" refId="B44" refString="Phookamsak, R, Liu, JK, McKenzie, EHC, Manamgoda, DS, Ariyawansa, H, Thambugala, KM, Dai, DQ, Camporesi, E, Chukeatirote, E, Wijayawardene, NN, Bahkali, AH, Mortimer, PE, Xu, JC, Hyde, KD, 2014. Revision of Phaeosphaeriaceae. . Fungal Diversity 68: 159 - 238" title="Revision of Phaeosphaeriaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-014-0308-3" volume="68" year="2014">Phookamsak et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName id="FADE6F866190F87F45B4A718CE0BBA99" family="Shiraiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Shiraiaceae</taxonomicName>
, ascostromata have multiple ascomata. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="4E00515FB913C54BE20F15489F6AF000" family="Shiraiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Shiraiaceae</taxonomicName>
produces a high quantity of hypocrellins and no such metabolites, secreted by 
<taxonomicName id="09A0551AAA682E4DEBCF4388CBBB5767" family="Phaeosphaeriaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Phaeosphaeriaceae</taxonomicName>
, were reported as far as we know (
<bibRefCitation id="8754E944F533B88890BB1796FE2652FD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-014-0308-3" author="Phookamsak, R" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="159 - 238" refId="B44" refString="Phookamsak, R, Liu, JK, McKenzie, EHC, Manamgoda, DS, Ariyawansa, H, Thambugala, KM, Dai, DQ, Camporesi, E, Chukeatirote, E, Wijayawardene, NN, Bahkali, AH, Mortimer, PE, Xu, JC, Hyde, KD, 2014. Revision of Phaeosphaeriaceae. . Fungal Diversity 68: 159 - 238" title="Revision of Phaeosphaeriaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-014-0308-3" volume="68" year="2014">Phookamsak et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, the third genus (i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="445484E6F20DB00BCC8CD81A3F86BB35" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Shiraiaceae" genus="Rubroshiraia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Rubroshiraia" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Rubroshiraia</taxonomicName>
) is introduced to the family and produces hypocrellins. The endophytic strains in the phylogenetic tree in Figure (2) probably can be named as new genera, once the types are selected. Thus, currently three genera are placed in 
<taxonomicName id="54DDFEF2495A65A63059E4C236AA8F41" family="Shiraiaceae" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Shiraiaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
